      "span_text": "The amphotericin-perforated-patch voltage-clamp technique was used for all studies to avoid unpredictable cell swelling and changes in membrane currents that often slowly occur with ruptured patches.  19 Amphotericin B (Sigma Chemical Co) was freshly dissolved in DMSO (Sigma) and then diluted in electrode filling solution to give final amphotericin and DMSO concentrations of 100 g/mL and 0.2% (vol/vol), respectively.",
